1
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:07,680
If you catch that bandit,
you'll hand him over to the police, right?

2
00:02:07,760 --> 00:02:11,960
<i>If there's no justice in this world,</i>
<i>then I'll use my way.</i>

3
00:02:12,040 --> 00:02:14,840
An eye for an eye, a tooth for a tooth.

4
00:02:14,920 --> 00:02:16,280
<i>You disappeared for an entire year.</i>

5
00:02:16,880 --> 00:02:19,600
And now you're Sir Lasor,
Governor's Assistant.

6
00:02:19,680 --> 00:02:22,920
Both Bandit Wad and Lasor have been
completely cleared of all charges.

7
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:24,240
<i>Because I am</i>

8
00:02:24,320 --> 00:02:26,920
Khun Yod's son,
Village Chief of Khuan Phra-ngam.

9
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:31,040
<i>Khun Yod's son isn't dead.</i>
<i>Can you tell me where to find him?</i>

10
00:02:31,560 --> 00:02:33,120
I want to meet him.

11
00:02:33,200 --> 00:02:35,920
<i>There is no Blur anymore. Only Yiam,</i>

12
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:39,040
Khun Yod's son, whose entire family
was slaughtered by Bandit Wad and his son.

13
00:02:39,120 --> 00:02:42,400
My father and brother didn't do it.

14
00:02:42,480 --> 00:02:44,960
<i>Of course you'd side with them.</i>

15
00:02:45,040 --> 00:02:46,480
<i>Blood is always thicker than water.</i>

16
00:02:56,680 --> 00:02:58,240
From now on,

17
00:03:00,840 --> 00:03:03,600
let's pretend we never knew each other.

18
00:03:19,760 --> 00:03:21,440
I already belong to you.

19
00:03:23,200 --> 00:03:24,720
You're really going to

20
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:27,600
abandon me?

21
00:03:38,200 --> 00:03:42,080
I can't force myself to love the daughter
of the ones who killed my family.

22
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:47,200
All this time,

23
00:03:47,880 --> 00:03:49,480
did you ever love me at all?

24
00:03:59,760 --> 00:04:02,120
I'm sorry
for everything I ever did to you.

25
00:04:06,760 --> 00:04:09,200
And for what I'm about to do
to your father and brother.

26
00:04:13,120 --> 00:04:15,000
If words won't get through to you,

27
00:04:19,200 --> 00:04:20,800
then you'll have to
step over my dead body first.

28
00:04:21,920 --> 00:04:25,320
I will never allow you
to lay a hand on my dad or Lasor.

29
00:04:31,760 --> 00:04:32,960
You can't stop me.

30
00:04:33,680 --> 00:04:37,800
Your father and your brother
must pay for what they did to my family.

31
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:45,160
Yiam! Come back!

32
00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:27,240
I only want Chin Seng himself.

33
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:29,680
As for his valuables, they're all yours.

34
00:05:31,640 --> 00:05:33,520
Make it look like a robbery.

35
00:05:34,280 --> 00:05:35,520
And remember.

36
00:05:36,120 --> 00:05:38,080
Do nothing beyond my orders.

37
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:40,080
As for Chin Seng,

38
00:05:40,160 --> 00:05:42,520
I'll get the truth
out of his mouth myself.

39
00:05:43,960 --> 00:05:45,480
Got it.

40
00:05:45,560 --> 00:05:48,360
When it comes to robbing,
you can count on us.

41
00:05:51,720 --> 00:05:52,720
Bandits,

42
00:05:53,480 --> 00:05:54,400
let's go.

43
00:06:16,880 --> 00:06:18,600
- Where are you going?
- Let go!

44
00:06:22,560 --> 00:06:24,880
Ugh!

45
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:28,560
Stop!

46
00:06:30,080 --> 00:06:33,640
If you don't want to die,
don't scream, pretty girl.

47
00:06:44,360 --> 00:06:45,480
Hey.

48
00:06:45,560 --> 00:06:47,760
Get everything out.

49
00:06:48,280 --> 00:06:51,080
Then what about this pretty one?

50
00:07:05,960 --> 00:07:08,200
I'll take you to heaven.

51
00:07:13,400 --> 00:07:14,320
Hey.

52
00:07:17,960 --> 00:07:19,200
If I didn't give the order,

53
00:07:20,240 --> 00:07:21,720
don't you dare even think about it.

54
00:08:09,120 --> 00:08:10,680
Hey!

55
00:08:13,280 --> 00:08:15,520
Are you the triad leader?

56
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:18,200
No.

57
00:08:18,280 --> 00:08:19,120
Are you sure?

58
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:22,800
I'm sure.

59
00:08:22,880 --> 00:08:24,040
- Hey!
- Watch out.

60
00:08:24,120 --> 00:08:25,080
Ugh!

61
00:08:31,160 --> 00:08:32,360
Ugh!

62
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:39,679
Hey!

63
00:08:42,320 --> 00:08:43,280
Why did you shoot him?!

64
00:08:43,360 --> 00:08:45,160
I just followed the governor's orders.

65
00:08:46,680 --> 00:08:49,360
Chin Seng wasn't part of the triad.
Duang deceived me.

66
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:52,240
Don't talk now.
Let's get out of here first.

67
00:08:54,240 --> 00:08:55,200
Ugh!

68
00:09:01,160 --> 00:09:02,240
Hey!

69
00:09:10,640 --> 00:09:11,600
Who are you?

70
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:15,520
The one who's going to drag you
before the court and have you beheaded.

71
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:17,160
Huh.

72
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:27,280
Ugh!

73
00:09:34,720 --> 00:09:36,040
Not bad.

74
00:09:36,840 --> 00:09:38,120
Now this is getting interesting.

75
00:09:44,280 --> 00:09:45,800
Let me see your face.

76
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:34,280
Tonight, I'm stripping you
of your sorcery, Lasor.

77
00:10:35,520 --> 00:10:38,760
Without your magic,
you're nothing but a mangy dog.

78
00:10:41,360 --> 00:10:42,840
Oh.

79
00:10:44,600 --> 00:10:45,960
It's you.

80
00:10:46,560 --> 00:10:48,000
You must be disappointed I'm still alive.

81
00:10:50,800 --> 00:10:52,080
Whether you live or die

82
00:10:52,640 --> 00:10:54,560
means nothing to my life.

83
00:10:55,160 --> 00:10:57,360
But I won't let you
and your father walk free.

84
00:10:57,960 --> 00:10:59,080
Then come on!

85
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:34,920
I'll make you taste the same agony

86
00:11:37,480 --> 00:11:39,360
you caused my father.

87
00:11:42,720 --> 00:11:44,040
Don't come any closer!

88
00:12:17,720 --> 00:12:18,800
Bandit Wad…

89
00:12:20,160 --> 00:12:21,360
It's good you came.

90
00:12:22,720 --> 00:12:24,680
I'll settle this with both of you at once.

91
00:12:24,760 --> 00:12:26,360
It's not what you think.

92
00:12:27,520 --> 00:12:28,520
Who's there?

93
00:12:54,680 --> 00:12:56,160
- Noree!
- Pun!

94
00:12:56,240 --> 00:12:57,360
- Help me.
- Noree.

95
00:12:57,880 --> 00:12:59,640
What happened?

96
00:12:59,720 --> 00:13:01,200
Bandits… bandits broke in.

97
00:13:01,280 --> 00:13:02,440
Are you hurt?

98
00:13:02,520 --> 00:13:03,960
I'm fine.

99
00:13:04,040 --> 00:13:05,680
Calm down, Noree.

100
00:13:05,760 --> 00:13:07,720
- Pun. Pun.
- Hm?

101
00:13:07,800 --> 00:13:08,800
Chin Seng.

102
00:13:11,480 --> 00:13:12,720
Pa.

103
00:13:16,720 --> 00:13:18,080
Pa! Pa!

104
00:13:19,760 --> 00:13:21,040
Pa!

105
00:13:23,600 --> 00:13:24,800
Pa!

106
00:13:25,480 --> 00:13:28,120
Pa!

107
00:13:32,360 --> 00:13:35,200
Pa! Wake up!

108
00:13:37,120 --> 00:13:38,680
Pa!

109
00:13:44,200 --> 00:13:46,160
Pa, wake up.

110
00:13:51,160 --> 00:13:53,560
Dad. Dad.

111
00:13:55,320 --> 00:13:57,120
I'm here, Pa.

112
00:13:57,920 --> 00:14:00,800
Pa.

113
00:14:01,400 --> 00:14:02,520
Pa.

114
00:14:18,320 --> 00:14:19,240
Ugh.

115
00:14:23,400 --> 00:14:26,600
Bandit Wad. You won't escape me for long.

116
00:14:39,120 --> 00:14:41,040
I'll hunt you down.

117
00:14:41,680 --> 00:14:43,760
Both of you.

118
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:01,280
PATROL UNIT

119
00:15:01,360 --> 00:15:02,560
Yes.

120
00:15:03,760 --> 00:15:06,040
The eyebrows were thick.

121
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:09,280
Like this?

122
00:15:10,920 --> 00:15:13,240
Yes, that's him.
He's the one who raided Chin Seng's house.

123
00:15:22,880 --> 00:15:24,000
It's Pae…

124
00:15:25,960 --> 00:15:27,120
Bandit Pud's nephew.

125
00:15:29,960 --> 00:15:32,920
As for the leader, I didn't see his face.

126
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:35,240
But I remember

127
00:15:36,160 --> 00:15:38,160
his fingernails were black.
It was terrifying.

128
00:15:43,760 --> 00:15:45,320
It has to be Lasor.

129
00:15:46,520 --> 00:15:48,880
Lasor and Pae are the Governor's men.

130
00:15:49,680 --> 00:15:50,880
Those bastards.

131
00:15:52,800 --> 00:15:55,240
They came to silence my father

132
00:15:55,960 --> 00:15:57,720
so the trail wouldn't lead back to them.

133
00:15:59,400 --> 00:16:01,280
Arresting Lasor won't be easy.

134
00:16:02,160 --> 00:16:04,000
You'll need sorcery.

135
00:16:06,480 --> 00:16:10,040
I've heard that sorcerers

136
00:16:10,120 --> 00:16:13,920
corrupted by their own curses
often develop black fingernails.

137
00:16:15,080 --> 00:16:16,520
If we can't catch Lasor yet,

138
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:18,520
we go after Bandit Pae.

139
00:16:22,160 --> 00:16:23,760
They're the governor's people.

140
00:16:24,800 --> 00:16:26,040
Even if we catch them,

141
00:16:26,120 --> 00:16:28,200
Duang will just release them,

142
00:16:30,080 --> 00:16:32,440
exactly like he did for Thongyoo and Song.

143
00:16:33,720 --> 00:16:35,160
Have you forgotten

144
00:16:36,600 --> 00:16:38,640
that my father died unjustly

145
00:16:39,840 --> 00:16:41,040
while his killers

146
00:16:41,880 --> 00:16:43,760
walked free?

147
00:16:50,360 --> 00:16:52,440
Now do you understand, Pun,

148
00:16:53,760 --> 00:16:55,800
how much this hurts?

149
00:17:05,839 --> 00:17:07,960
I'll capture Bandit Pae secretly

150
00:17:10,200 --> 00:17:14,200
and hand him over
to the Provincial Patrol Department.

151
00:17:15,400 --> 00:17:18,839
This time,
Duang won't be able to protect him.

152
00:17:20,640 --> 00:17:22,640
Then we'll trace it back to Lasor

153
00:17:23,680 --> 00:17:25,319
and whoever is pulling his strings.

154
00:17:29,800 --> 00:17:31,720
Spread out. Search everywhere.

155
00:17:32,280 --> 00:17:34,040
We must capture Bandit Pae.

156
00:17:55,080 --> 00:17:57,320
Our informants say

157
00:17:57,400 --> 00:18:01,200
the police have figured it out
it was Lasor and Pae.

158
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:05,440
They're hunting them down to hand them
over to the Provincial Patrol.

159
00:18:06,120 --> 00:18:11,360
They mess up even something this simple.
We'll all be screwed.

160
00:18:20,200 --> 00:18:23,720
So where are Lasor and Pae now?

161
00:18:25,040 --> 00:18:28,000
They've likely gone into hiding.

162
00:18:32,240 --> 00:18:34,360
Send men to silence them

163
00:18:35,200 --> 00:18:37,040
before the police get to them.

164
00:18:39,840 --> 00:18:41,840
Getting rid of Pae is easy,

165
00:18:42,440 --> 00:18:44,080
but what about Lasor?

166
00:18:58,240 --> 00:18:59,680
We can't let him live.

167
00:19:00,840 --> 00:19:03,200
I'll write to my superior.

168
00:19:04,080 --> 00:19:06,440
He's a high-ranking noble in the capital.

169
00:19:06,520 --> 00:19:09,120
I'll have him send down
a powerful sorcerer.

170
00:19:09,640 --> 00:19:11,600
One who can deal with Lasor.

171
00:19:13,280 --> 00:19:16,280
Tim, go deal with Pae immediately.

172
00:19:16,360 --> 00:19:18,160
Make sure he never opens his mouth.

173
00:19:18,240 --> 00:19:19,320
Yes, sir.

174
00:20:05,160 --> 00:20:06,200
Bandit Wad…

175
00:20:07,960 --> 00:20:10,160
Even if I can't kill you
with my own hands,

176
00:20:11,240 --> 00:20:14,120
I'll use the law
to deal with scum like you.

177
00:20:18,160 --> 00:20:20,800
I'll drag you two down

178
00:20:20,880 --> 00:20:22,840
to face the karma you created.

179
00:21:07,680 --> 00:21:08,800
Dad…

180
00:21:28,360 --> 00:21:31,240
Drink this.
It'll help with the internal injuries.

181
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:52,160
What were you doing
at Chin Seng's house last night?

182
00:21:55,680 --> 00:21:58,720
Duang tricked me.
He said Chin Seng was a triad leader

183
00:21:59,640 --> 00:22:01,400
and ordered me to kill him.

184
00:22:04,160 --> 00:22:05,720
I shouldn't have believed him, Dad.

185
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:11,120
Duang is a two-faced snake.

186
00:22:12,800 --> 00:22:14,720
You should never have gotten involved
with him in the first place.

187
00:22:16,840 --> 00:22:18,120
I'll kill him.

188
00:22:23,640 --> 00:22:27,600
When will you stop causing trouble, Lasor?

189
00:22:31,240 --> 00:22:33,440
Right now, Yiam misunderstands everything.

190
00:22:33,520 --> 00:22:37,760
He thinks you and I
murdered his entire family,

191
00:22:39,320 --> 00:22:41,600
when Khun Yod was actually my dear friend.

192
00:22:42,560 --> 00:22:44,440
Someone must be manipulating Yiam.

193
00:22:47,720 --> 00:22:49,560
Do you know who started this, Lasor?

194
00:22:50,080 --> 00:22:51,200
No.

195
00:22:52,120 --> 00:22:53,520
I don't know, Dad.

196
00:23:01,520 --> 00:23:04,640
I haven't seen you for a long time.

197
00:23:05,520 --> 00:23:06,800
Where did you go?

198
00:23:10,560 --> 00:23:11,640
Hm?

199
00:23:14,120 --> 00:23:15,720
I went to train…

200
00:23:17,480 --> 00:23:18,960
with a wandering monk in the forest.

201
00:23:19,480 --> 00:23:23,160
What kind of monk teaches sorcery?
Don't lie to me.

202
00:23:23,720 --> 00:23:26,320
Who taught you that magic?

203
00:23:31,160 --> 00:23:32,240
Who?!

204
00:23:35,560 --> 00:23:37,120
A mystic on Khao Phrom.

205
00:23:38,400 --> 00:23:40,680
I don't know his name. He never told me.

206
00:23:44,200 --> 00:23:46,040
Then he must be a heretic,

207
00:23:47,640 --> 00:23:50,080
passing such depraved magic on to you.

208
00:23:50,160 --> 00:23:52,760
Look at yourself.

209
00:23:54,360 --> 00:23:56,040
Cursed by the dark arts,

210
00:23:56,120 --> 00:23:58,200
you're turning into a walking ghost.

211
00:23:58,280 --> 00:24:01,080
If this continues,
you'll either die or lose your mind.

212
00:24:01,160 --> 00:24:04,840
Why did you do this, Lasor?
Is this really what you wanted?

213
00:24:06,360 --> 00:24:07,760
Did I have a choice, Dad?

214
00:24:08,760 --> 00:24:10,160
You never taught me,

215
00:24:10,680 --> 00:24:12,120
so I had to find my own way.

216
00:24:12,760 --> 00:24:16,160
Dark magic or white magic,
it all gives you power over others.

217
00:24:16,880 --> 00:24:20,680
I wanted to prove I'm the son
of Bandit Wad. I'm not worthless.

218
00:24:20,760 --> 00:24:21,880
I wanted you to be proud of me.

219
00:24:21,960 --> 00:24:24,080
How many times
have you disappointed me already?

220
00:24:24,160 --> 00:24:25,240
How many times?

221
00:24:26,080 --> 00:24:29,200
And you still expect me to be proud? Huh?

222
00:24:31,720 --> 00:24:36,120
Even if you gain boundless power,
even if the world bows before you,

223
00:24:36,720 --> 00:24:39,840
if you have to suffer
like you're in hell itself,

224
00:24:39,920 --> 00:24:41,680
I will never be proud.

225
00:24:47,720 --> 00:24:49,560
Because I'm your father.

226
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:54,920
Every time you hurt,

227
00:24:56,400 --> 00:24:57,920
I hurt even more.

228
00:25:14,560 --> 00:25:15,560
Lasor…

229
00:25:19,720 --> 00:25:21,560
You don't need to do anything for me.

230
00:25:26,960 --> 00:25:28,080
I only want…

231
00:25:30,200 --> 00:25:31,360
Lasor…

232
00:25:33,880 --> 00:25:36,280
my old son back.

233
00:25:37,720 --> 00:25:39,360
That's enough for me.

234
00:25:42,320 --> 00:25:43,520
That's all I ask.

235
00:25:44,640 --> 00:25:45,600
Can you do that for me?

236
00:25:58,080 --> 00:25:59,000
Please, son.

237
00:26:12,560 --> 00:26:13,760
I'm sorry, Dad.

238
00:26:17,280 --> 00:26:18,480
But I've gone too far

239
00:26:19,600 --> 00:26:21,360
to turn back now.

240
00:26:26,960 --> 00:26:28,480
Change your path, Lasor.

241
00:26:30,120 --> 00:26:31,240
It's never too late.

242
00:26:33,400 --> 00:26:35,080
I'll find a way to help you.

243
00:26:43,240 --> 00:26:44,240
Please, my son.

244
00:26:50,680 --> 00:26:52,880
There's a lot of evidence linking Lasor

245
00:26:52,960 --> 00:26:55,760
to the robbery and murder of Chin Seng.

246
00:26:57,640 --> 00:27:00,240
The police are turning the land
upside down looking for him.

247
00:27:01,480 --> 00:27:03,800
Lasor was at the scene, yes,

248
00:27:03,880 --> 00:27:07,400
but the one who actually killed Chin Seng
could've been Bandit Pae.

249
00:27:07,920 --> 00:27:09,840
There has to be more to this.

250
00:27:10,800 --> 00:27:13,040
If Lasor didn't do it,
then why did he run?

251
00:27:14,800 --> 00:27:17,040
Someone must be pulling the strings.

252
00:27:18,360 --> 00:27:19,440
Or could this be

253
00:27:20,720 --> 00:27:22,360
the governor's orders?

254
00:27:22,880 --> 00:27:25,080
I need to get the truth from Lasor.

255
00:27:26,240 --> 00:27:28,000
Do you even know where he is?

256
00:27:31,320 --> 00:27:32,960
If it was the governor's order,

257
00:27:33,600 --> 00:27:35,840
Lasor might be hiding at the residence.

258
00:27:37,360 --> 00:27:38,640
I'll go with you.

259
00:27:38,720 --> 00:27:40,560
Uncle Niem,
please stay here with Uncle Chaem.

260
00:27:41,080 --> 00:27:42,880
I'll go find Lasor myself.

261
00:27:43,480 --> 00:27:47,600
I need the truth,
both about Chin Seng's death

262
00:27:48,640 --> 00:27:50,200
and about Yiam's family.

263
00:28:20,400 --> 00:28:22,240
Why are you following me?

264
00:28:24,280 --> 00:28:26,160
You're looking for Lasor, aren't you?

265
00:28:26,960 --> 00:28:28,720
I'm coming with you.

266
00:28:29,320 --> 00:28:33,040
Stay out of my brother's business.
Don't say I didn't warn you.

267
00:28:34,440 --> 00:28:36,040
Your brother is a ruthless bandit

268
00:28:37,520 --> 00:28:38,800
who murdered Chin Seng.

269
00:28:39,880 --> 00:28:41,680
And your father helped him escape.

270
00:28:42,560 --> 00:28:45,240
They conspired to kill Chin Seng

271
00:28:45,320 --> 00:28:46,520
and my family.

272
00:28:47,400 --> 00:28:49,400
How do you still have the nerve
to protect them?

273
00:28:51,080 --> 00:28:53,720
Don't make accusations
when you have no evidence.

274
00:28:53,800 --> 00:28:56,480
I am the evidence. I was there.

275
00:28:58,360 --> 00:29:00,200
I saw the vile things

276
00:29:00,280 --> 00:29:02,680
he did to Chin Seng and my family.

277
00:29:06,480 --> 00:29:09,080
Stop blindly taking his side.

278
00:29:11,320 --> 00:29:14,680
If Lasor is truly innocent,
tell him to surrender

279
00:29:15,800 --> 00:29:17,800
and I'll spare his life.

280
00:29:23,320 --> 00:29:24,320
Take me to him.

281
00:29:28,040 --> 00:29:29,720
Then you'll have to step over my dead body

282
00:29:34,680 --> 00:29:36,640
Don't think just because
you're a woman I wouldn't dare.

283
00:30:14,320 --> 00:30:16,640
I will find the evidence

284
00:30:16,720 --> 00:30:18,200
that forces you to accept the truth.

285
00:30:19,880 --> 00:30:23,120
Then your eyes will finally open
and you'll stop siding with them.

286
00:30:25,320 --> 00:30:26,240
No.

287
00:30:28,040 --> 00:30:31,000
I'll find the evidence
to prove their innocence too.

288
00:30:31,640 --> 00:30:34,880
I'll clear them of your accusations.

289
00:30:39,160 --> 00:30:40,560
But until then,

290
00:30:41,160 --> 00:30:43,560
please don't hurt my father or my brother.

291
00:30:47,720 --> 00:30:48,800
I'm begging you.

292
00:30:54,280 --> 00:30:56,120
I will never let my heart soften again.

293
00:31:12,640 --> 00:31:14,400
You have your beliefs,

294
00:31:14,480 --> 00:31:16,480
and I have mine.

295
00:31:17,960 --> 00:31:19,560
Our paths

296
00:31:20,440 --> 00:31:21,960
will never cross again.

297
00:31:26,040 --> 00:31:27,840
I'll prove to you

298
00:31:27,920 --> 00:31:31,320
that Dad and Lasor
are not the men you think they are.

299
00:31:42,760 --> 00:31:44,040
Dad!

300
00:31:49,120 --> 00:31:50,160
Ugh!

301
00:31:56,200 --> 00:31:57,160
Pae.

302
00:32:09,880 --> 00:32:10,840
Hey!

303
00:32:28,400 --> 00:32:29,480
Pae!

304
00:32:49,880 --> 00:32:51,040
Those are Tim's men.

305
00:33:07,360 --> 00:33:10,360
Help me. I'm one of the governor's men.

306
00:33:16,280 --> 00:33:18,800
I'm one of you!
Why are you trying to kill me?

307
00:33:19,320 --> 00:33:21,120
Orders from my boss.

308
00:33:23,080 --> 00:33:25,000
Duang, you bastard.

309
00:33:25,800 --> 00:33:26,800
Die.

310
00:33:33,120 --> 00:33:34,320
Ugh!

311
00:33:51,000 --> 00:33:52,120
You again?

312
00:33:53,760 --> 00:33:54,720
Come with me.

313
00:33:56,080 --> 00:33:57,080
Where are you taking me?

314
00:33:58,600 --> 00:34:01,680
Turn yourself in and I'll spare your life.

315
00:34:03,720 --> 00:34:06,680
And if I refuse?
What are you going to do to me?

316
00:34:14,120 --> 00:34:16,080
Are you coming or not?

317
00:34:17,040 --> 00:34:18,159
Huh?!

318
00:34:22,040 --> 00:34:24,560
I'll go! I'll go!

319
00:34:32,120 --> 00:34:33,360
Turn yourself in.

320
00:34:33,960 --> 00:34:37,719
Confess to the police about
every vile thing you and Lasor have done.

321
00:34:38,880 --> 00:34:40,199
If you keep your mouth shut,

322
00:34:40,840 --> 00:34:44,679
Duang will just send someone else.
Next time, you won't survive.

323
00:34:45,880 --> 00:34:49,560
Duang is the one behind everything.
He gives the orders

324
00:34:50,199 --> 00:34:52,400
and he has all the power.
Who could possibly touch him?

325
00:34:52,480 --> 00:34:53,600
I can.

326
00:34:56,280 --> 00:34:58,080
I'll make sure
he never gets another chance to do evil.

327
00:35:09,680 --> 00:35:11,000
Hey! What's that?!

328
00:35:13,000 --> 00:35:14,040
Hey.

329
00:35:21,080 --> 00:35:22,240
It hurts!

330
00:35:24,520 --> 00:35:27,400
Some masked guy
dumped him right in front of the station.

331
00:35:28,920 --> 00:35:30,080
Who was it?

332
00:35:30,160 --> 00:35:32,320
No idea.

333
00:35:32,880 --> 00:35:36,720
But it's probably the same man
we saw at Chin Seng's house.

334
00:35:55,640 --> 00:35:57,360
You killed my father, didn't you?

335
00:36:03,120 --> 00:36:05,960
You already know the answer. Why ask?

336
00:36:07,320 --> 00:36:08,320
I'll kill you!

337
00:36:08,400 --> 00:36:10,000
You worthless piece of filth!

338
00:36:10,080 --> 00:36:12,800
Calm down. We're officers of the law.

339
00:36:14,240 --> 00:36:15,400
Who did you rob with?

340
00:36:16,200 --> 00:36:17,360
It was Lasor, wasn't it?

341
00:36:21,840 --> 00:36:23,160
Even if I told you,

342
00:36:23,840 --> 00:36:25,760
you wouldn't be able to touch him anyway.

343
00:36:31,200 --> 00:36:32,560
Get him up.

344
00:36:39,760 --> 00:36:42,920
Unless you want every tooth
knocked out of your mouth.

345
00:36:44,960 --> 00:36:46,760
I'll tell you. I'll tell you.

346
00:36:48,520 --> 00:36:49,680
Who?!

347
00:36:51,640 --> 00:36:53,480
The one who robbed the house with me

348
00:36:54,400 --> 00:36:55,600
was…

349
00:37:09,880 --> 00:37:12,840
Remember, from now on,

350
00:37:12,920 --> 00:37:15,680
I am your master.

351
00:37:58,400 --> 00:37:59,920
Looking for Lasor?

352
00:38:15,080 --> 00:38:16,200
It's you.

353
00:38:17,320 --> 00:38:18,640
Is my brother here?

354
00:38:23,520 --> 00:38:24,440
Hey!

355
00:38:24,520 --> 00:38:25,840
What are you doing? Let go!

356
00:38:37,080 --> 00:38:38,080
Take her.

357
00:38:46,520 --> 00:38:47,760
Was it done?

358
00:38:47,840 --> 00:38:50,720
A black-masked man showed up
and helped Pae escape, sir.

359
00:38:54,520 --> 00:38:55,840
That black-masked man?

360
00:38:57,760 --> 00:38:58,920
Again?

361
00:39:10,600 --> 00:39:12,720
Between your sorcery and Father Wad,

362
00:39:13,480 --> 00:39:14,480
what will you choose?

363
00:39:21,080 --> 00:39:22,520
I've disappointed Dad my whole life.

364
00:39:24,640 --> 00:39:25,680
This time,

365
00:39:26,880 --> 00:39:27,920
I don't want to fail him.

366
00:39:28,520 --> 00:39:30,040
But if you cleanse the sorcery,

367
00:39:30,960 --> 00:39:32,560
you'll become an ordinary man.

368
00:39:33,640 --> 00:39:36,000
Are you really going to let
all your efforts come to nothing?

369
00:39:38,040 --> 00:39:39,160
Nui…

370
00:39:41,960 --> 00:39:44,000
you gave up your life for me,

371
00:39:48,080 --> 00:39:49,920
and I couldn't even keep this power.

372
00:39:53,360 --> 00:39:54,840
But I really am a terrible son.

373
00:39:57,280 --> 00:39:58,880
I've disappointed my father all the time.

374
00:40:01,480 --> 00:40:02,800
Since I was a child,

375
00:40:05,240 --> 00:40:07,160
I've disappointed him countless times.

376
00:40:13,280 --> 00:40:14,320
But this time,

377
00:40:15,800 --> 00:40:17,400
I won't let him down again.

378
00:40:19,680 --> 00:40:21,080
You're sure about this?

379
00:40:27,560 --> 00:40:28,600
I'm sorry.

380
00:40:30,280 --> 00:40:32,000
I've made my decision.

381
00:40:33,200 --> 00:40:36,720
I'm going back
to be the son my father deserves.

382
00:40:39,400 --> 00:40:40,640
I understand.

383
00:40:42,400 --> 00:40:43,840
No matter what you choose,

384
00:40:43,920 --> 00:40:46,440
I'll always stand by you.

385
00:41:09,600 --> 00:41:10,600
Master.

386
00:41:14,960 --> 00:41:17,560
Removing the sorcery from your son

387
00:41:17,640 --> 00:41:20,520
will not be easy. Are you certain?

388
00:41:24,040 --> 00:41:26,840
It's the only way to save Lasor.

389
00:41:31,240 --> 00:41:34,680
And what if he strays again?
What if he returns to his old ways?

390
00:41:39,280 --> 00:41:41,640
This time,
I will erase his memories entirely.

391
00:41:42,840 --> 00:41:44,680
He will remember nothing.

392
00:41:48,400 --> 00:41:50,040
Not even…

393
00:41:52,120 --> 00:41:53,520
who his parents are.

394
00:41:55,600 --> 00:41:57,480
He'll start a new life.

395
00:41:58,680 --> 00:42:00,560
I'll shave his head, ordain him as a monk,

396
00:42:01,440 --> 00:42:02,840
and put him on a junk ship

397
00:42:03,520 --> 00:42:06,400
to a land far across the seas.

398
00:42:07,920 --> 00:42:09,040
The saffron robes

399
00:42:09,840 --> 00:42:12,360
will protect him.

400
00:42:12,440 --> 00:42:16,040
Past karma has already written his fate.

401
00:42:20,080 --> 00:42:22,720
While new karma can alter it,

402
00:42:23,960 --> 00:42:25,640
but what you choose to do next

403
00:42:25,720 --> 00:42:28,000
depends entirely on your son,

404
00:42:28,640 --> 00:42:32,480
not on you
deciding the course of his life.

405
00:42:38,640 --> 00:42:41,480
My son's life is at stake.

406
00:42:43,600 --> 00:42:47,560
I will defy fate to save him.

407
00:43:19,080 --> 00:43:21,520
I will perform
the ritual of consecrated water

408
00:43:22,320 --> 00:43:24,680
to purge this vile curse from your body.

409
00:43:25,720 --> 00:43:26,800
During the ritual,

410
00:43:27,320 --> 00:43:29,840
the dark sorcery will turn inward
and devour you,

411
00:43:30,640 --> 00:43:33,040
it will be unbearable agony.

412
00:43:33,800 --> 00:43:35,360
But no matter what happens,

413
00:43:36,040 --> 00:43:38,400
you must not step outside
the boundary of the holy thread

414
00:43:39,760 --> 00:43:42,480
until I complete the cleansing.

415
00:43:43,320 --> 00:43:44,280
Are you ready, Lasor?

416
00:43:48,440 --> 00:43:49,520
I'm ready, Dad.

417
00:43:54,200 --> 00:43:55,480
Then I'll begin.

418
00:44:29,760 --> 00:44:31,600
It hurts, Dad!

419
00:44:44,160 --> 00:44:45,760
Endure it, Lasor.

420
00:44:45,840 --> 00:44:47,520
- Endure it.
- Can we stop?

421
00:44:56,320 --> 00:44:58,960
I can't take it anymore!

422
00:44:59,560 --> 00:45:00,520
Lasor!

423
00:45:09,920 --> 00:45:12,040
Lasor!

424
00:45:18,200 --> 00:45:19,520
Dad!

425
00:45:19,600 --> 00:45:22,680
I can't take it anymore. Let me go.

426
00:45:22,760 --> 00:45:23,960
Lasor!

427
00:45:24,840 --> 00:45:27,080
This curse will ruin your life!

428
00:45:28,160 --> 00:45:30,040
Let me finish the ritual.

429
00:45:30,120 --> 00:45:32,480
Dad, please let me go.

430
00:45:33,200 --> 00:45:34,360
I beg you.

431
00:45:35,040 --> 00:45:37,080
Lasor, come back, my son.

432
00:45:37,800 --> 00:45:38,680
Come back.

433
00:45:39,840 --> 00:45:42,520
Please. I'm dying, Dad.

434
00:45:44,240 --> 00:45:45,360
Lasor!

435
00:45:50,800 --> 00:45:54,440
<i>Vathono amamavava.</i>

436
00:46:16,240 --> 00:46:18,360
<i>I will draw up</i>
<i>All holy incantations to my throat</i>

437
00:46:18,440 --> 00:46:21,400
<i>I will lift</i>
<i>All holy incantations above my chest</i>

438
00:46:21,920 --> 00:46:24,160
<i>I will raise</i>
<i>All holy incantations above my head</i>

439
00:46:26,000 --> 00:46:28,000
<i>The venerable master therefore</i>
<i>Makes me supreme above all men</i>

440
00:46:29,240 --> 00:46:31,920
<i>Ehi klai klai, piyan ma-ma.</i>

441
00:47:00,080 --> 00:47:01,280
Corpse-crows?

442
00:47:07,040 --> 00:47:08,480
<i>Ni so sa a.</i>

443
00:47:24,520 --> 00:47:25,560
Lasor?

444
00:47:28,080 --> 00:47:29,160
Lasor!

445
00:47:30,320 --> 00:47:31,360
Lasor!

446
00:47:42,520 --> 00:47:44,600
Lasor, come back!

447
00:47:45,960 --> 00:47:47,080
Lasor!

448
00:48:04,000 --> 00:48:04,920
Master…

449
00:48:07,360 --> 00:48:08,920
Master, I'm in pain…

450
00:48:10,240 --> 00:48:12,360
Well, Lasor?

451
00:48:12,960 --> 00:48:14,760
Are you close to death yet?

452
00:48:15,680 --> 00:48:16,840
Master…

453
00:48:18,080 --> 00:48:19,920
Please… help me.

454
00:48:20,000 --> 00:48:23,600
<i>O eka o turako o devi.</i>

455
00:48:44,360 --> 00:48:47,240
How about now? Feeling better?

456
00:49:07,760 --> 00:49:10,600
Thank you, Master. You saved my life.

457
00:49:13,240 --> 00:49:14,240
Lasor,

458
00:49:14,920 --> 00:49:17,560
how many times have I saved you now?
Do you even remember?

459
00:49:20,280 --> 00:49:24,280
I could never repay you in this lifetime.

460
00:49:25,680 --> 00:49:27,400
But I must go back
and take revenge on Duang

461
00:49:28,680 --> 00:49:30,320
for deceiving me.

462
00:49:34,520 --> 00:49:36,280
Duang is a small-time fool.

463
00:49:37,360 --> 00:49:38,760
He's nothing compared to your father.

464
00:49:39,960 --> 00:49:41,400
What does he have to do with this?

465
00:49:44,960 --> 00:49:46,520
I'll tell you this out of kindness.

466
00:49:47,640 --> 00:49:48,760
Your father

467
00:49:50,120 --> 00:49:53,360
didn't just want to cleanse your sorcery.

468
00:49:53,960 --> 00:49:56,840
He planned to erase
your memories entirely.

469
00:49:59,240 --> 00:50:02,880
What kind of father
does that to his own son?

470
00:50:06,080 --> 00:50:07,040
That's not true.

471
00:50:08,160 --> 00:50:09,520
Why would he do that?

472
00:50:13,880 --> 00:50:15,320
He knows

473
00:50:15,840 --> 00:50:18,560
he can't stop
your destined rise to greatness,

474
00:50:19,160 --> 00:50:20,840
so he planned to wipe your mind clean.

475
00:50:20,920 --> 00:50:24,400
He wanted a new Lasor
who remembers nothing.

476
00:50:28,040 --> 00:50:29,320
Tell me,

477
00:50:31,000 --> 00:50:33,160
if he's willing to do that to you,

478
00:50:33,760 --> 00:50:36,440
how can you still call him your father?

479
00:50:43,960 --> 00:50:45,080
That's not true.

480
00:50:47,040 --> 00:50:49,760
My father wouldn't be that cruel.

481
00:50:59,200 --> 00:51:03,160
I should've let him erase your memory
and be done with it.

482
00:51:03,240 --> 00:51:04,080
You idiot.

483
00:51:06,080 --> 00:51:07,440
Use your head for once.

484
00:51:17,160 --> 00:51:19,800
PATROL UNIT

485
00:51:19,880 --> 00:51:21,760
It sounds like
he was afflicted by dark magic.

486
00:51:24,360 --> 00:51:25,360
What do you mean, Dad?

487
00:51:28,360 --> 00:51:29,480
Bandits often

488
00:51:30,000 --> 00:51:32,160
perform oath rituals,
drinking holy water together.

489
00:51:32,840 --> 00:51:36,120
If anyone betrays their own,

490
00:51:36,760 --> 00:51:40,400
the sorcery inside that water
strikes back.

491
00:51:41,640 --> 00:51:43,720
Some are tortured to death.

492
00:51:46,080 --> 00:51:48,280
The elders call it
"breaking the water oath."

493
00:51:51,600 --> 00:51:53,320
Pae is a key witness.

494
00:51:54,200 --> 00:51:55,560
We can't let him die.

495
00:51:58,040 --> 00:51:59,760
But how did you catch him, Pun?

496
00:52:02,000 --> 00:52:03,680
A masked man dumped him
in front of the station.

497
00:52:05,240 --> 00:52:06,320
A masked man?

498
00:52:06,840 --> 00:52:08,040
Forget the masked man for now.

499
00:52:09,360 --> 00:52:11,320
We need to save Pae.

500
00:52:12,160 --> 00:52:15,440
Uncle Chaem, you were ordained,
do you know a way to break this curse?

501
00:52:24,400 --> 00:52:25,400
Chang,

502
00:52:26,400 --> 00:52:28,120
fetch me a bowl of water.

503
00:52:29,480 --> 00:52:30,480
Okay.

504
00:52:40,400 --> 00:52:43,800
Help me…

505
00:52:44,840 --> 00:52:46,680
It hurts. I can't take it anymore…

506
00:52:56,280 --> 00:52:59,920
<i>Na kloan mo thon, phut klon tha thon,</i>

507
00:53:00,000 --> 00:53:02,520
<i>ya lut loy luean,</i>
<i>kluan duai Namo Buddhaya…</i>

508
00:53:08,400 --> 00:53:09,560
Give this to him.

509
00:53:35,160 --> 00:53:36,240
A leech?

510
00:53:37,680 --> 00:53:39,000
A buffalo leech, Dad.

511
00:53:39,760 --> 00:53:41,920
Yes. I see it.

512
00:53:46,240 --> 00:53:49,640
Pae will wake up soon,
and then you'll learn the whole truth.

513
00:53:50,800 --> 00:53:54,960
I want to drag Lasor and his men
to justice so badly I can't stand it.

514
00:53:55,480 --> 00:53:57,800
And if the law can't touch them?

515
00:53:59,120 --> 00:54:00,840
Then we'll deal with them
with mob justice.

516
00:54:03,480 --> 00:54:05,920
Whatever you do,
remember that police uniform you wear.

517
00:54:07,160 --> 00:54:09,480
It was bestowed by the Crown.

518
00:54:11,880 --> 00:54:13,920
Never forget your duty,

519
00:54:14,000 --> 00:54:17,480
to uphold the law, protect the land,

520
00:54:18,040 --> 00:54:21,560
relieve suffering, and serve the people.

521
00:54:22,280 --> 00:54:23,880
Never disgrace it.

522
00:54:26,360 --> 00:54:27,640
I became an officer

523
00:54:28,680 --> 00:54:30,640
to serve with honor.

524
00:54:31,800 --> 00:54:33,640
No matter how hard

525
00:54:34,240 --> 00:54:36,320
or how dangerous it gets,

526
00:54:37,400 --> 00:54:39,560
I'll protect that honor with my life.

527
00:54:40,760 --> 00:54:41,920
Mm.

528
00:55:05,480 --> 00:55:06,560
Lasor.

529
00:55:07,760 --> 00:55:09,520
I'm warning you about your enemy.

530
00:55:10,280 --> 00:55:11,960
You mean Yiam, Master?

531
00:55:15,760 --> 00:55:19,080
You can't defeat him
because he carries something sacred.

532
00:55:19,600 --> 00:55:21,200
What is it, Master?

533
00:55:22,240 --> 00:55:24,080
Klaikot Lek Lai.

534
00:55:24,160 --> 00:55:26,960
It's a holy element
that makes blades and bullets useless.

535
00:55:30,920 --> 00:55:32,240
Then I'll just take it from him.

536
00:55:32,760 --> 00:55:34,520
Hey, it's not that simple.

537
00:55:36,000 --> 00:55:39,720
Klaikot Lek Lai
is forged by a righteous hermit.

538
00:55:39,800 --> 00:55:42,200
Don't you evil men dare possess it.

539
00:55:47,280 --> 00:55:51,240
Rip the Lek Lai out of his body.
Then you can kill him.

540
00:55:58,320 --> 00:55:59,320
Understand?

541
00:56:03,080 --> 00:56:04,120
Yiam…

542
00:56:24,200 --> 00:56:26,200
I'll have to eliminate
everyone who knows the truth,

543
00:56:27,680 --> 00:56:28,680
Yiam,

544
00:56:29,480 --> 00:56:30,480
Pae,

545
00:56:32,240 --> 00:56:35,280
Tim, Duang.

546
00:56:37,080 --> 00:56:39,560
All secrets must die with you.

547
00:56:43,840 --> 00:56:46,120
Dad must never learn the truth.

548
00:56:51,920 --> 00:56:55,520
Yiwha went to look for Lasor
at the governor's residence yesterday.

549
00:56:55,600 --> 00:56:57,520
- Where are you going?
- To find proof

550
00:56:57,600 --> 00:57:00,040
that my father and my brother
aren't the monsters you claim they are.

551
00:57:02,760 --> 00:57:03,960
Hey!

552
00:57:04,040 --> 00:57:06,800
You're the one
who ordered Chin Seng's death, aren't you?

553
00:57:06,880 --> 00:57:08,280
There's been an order from above.

554
00:57:08,360 --> 00:57:09,400
From who?

555
00:57:09,480 --> 00:57:13,960
<i>I was cleansing Lasor of the dark magic.</i>
<i>Someone sent corpse-crows to take him.</i>

556
00:57:14,560 --> 00:57:16,240
<i>Take them to the residence</i>
<i>for questioning.</i>

557
00:57:16,320 --> 00:57:17,360
Dad!

558
00:57:17,440 --> 00:57:20,920
Even if you go, you can't help.
They hold all the power.

559
00:57:22,360 --> 00:57:23,360
Ugh!

560
00:57:24,600 --> 00:57:27,600
Lasor, how dare you lay a hand on me?

561
00:57:28,200 --> 00:57:29,000
<i>Yiam, stop.</i>

562
00:57:29,080 --> 00:57:31,560
<i>You are a righteous man,</i>
<i>that is why you can wield the Lek Lai.</i>

563
00:57:31,640 --> 00:57:33,520
<i>But never use a sacred power for evil.</i>

564
00:57:33,600 --> 00:57:34,960
Or it will turn against you.

565
00:57:35,040 --> 00:57:38,400
I'd rather die!
I'll die right here with you!

566
00:58:23,080 --> 00:58:24,760
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
